      <Meanings>
        <Meaning id="c9618ee7-378b-4725-8250-cef384a82e8c" type="Noun">
          <Vi>kháng thể</Vi>
          <En>A protein produced by the immune system that identifies and neutralizes foreign objects like bacteria and viruses.</En>
          <Example>Monoclonal antibodies are used in targeted cancer therapies to bind specifically to tumor cells.</Example>
          <IsArchaic>false</IsArchaic>
          <Situations>
            <Situation id="c6ede99c-8951-4b20-8296-ef4ec9c5d102">
              <Vi>Một loại protein trong máu giúp cơ thể chống lại vi khuẩn và virus.</Vi>
              <En>A Y-shaped protein in the blood that recognizes and binds to specific antigens to help eliminate pathogens.</En>
            </Situation>
            <Situation id="e2928e3c-d116-4756-ae35-6a5c571a7dbd">
              <Vi>Được tạo ra bởi tế bào B trong phản ứng miễn dịch thích nghi.</Vi>
              <En>Produced by B cells during the adaptive immune response to combat specific pathogens.</En>
            </Situation>
          </Situations>
